@6050 = ~This blade is one of Haer'Dalis's favorite weapons. Made from green steel tempered from ore found only in the Nine Hells of Baator, this abyssal short sword is capable of inflicting additional poison damage if the target fails to resist it. This blade may only be used by tieflings.

STATISTICS:

Combat abilities:
– Hit target must Save vs. Poison at -1 or suffer 6 points of poison damage over 3 seconds
– Considered a +3 enchanted weapon for the purposes of what it can hit
– Attacks per round: +1/2

THAC0: +2
Damage: 1d6+2 (piercing)
Speed Factor: 0
Proficiency Type: Short Sword
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 4 Strength

Weight: 2~

@6051 = ~Chaos is a short sword usable only by tieflings. Every time it strikes an opponent, the target is temporarily weakened. Haer'Dalis prefers using Chaos with its partner—Entropy. When dual wielding these two blades, Haer'Dalis is a dangerous opponent.

STATISTICS:

Combat abilities:
– Touch of Chaos: For two rounds, hit target suffers a non-stacking -5 Dexterity penalty and one randomly chosen stacking -1 penalty to saving throws vs. Poison, Armor Class, THAC0, or Damage. Constructs such as golems are unaffected.
– Considered a +3 enchanted weapon for the purposes of what it can hit
– Attacks per round: +1/2

THAC0: +2
Damage: 1d6+2 (piercing)
Speed Factor: 0
Proficiency Type: Short Sword
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 4 Strength

Weight: 2~

