@7120 = ~This armor, long in the Corthala bloodline, protects the wearer against all forms of attacks. The armor is enchanted so that it grants a +3 bonus to Valygar's Armor Class. It also adds a bonus to resisting acid, fire, and magical damage. The armor also makes Valygar immune to charm while he wears it. As it is specially fitted for Valygar, only he may wear it.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Immunity to charm
– Fire, Acid, and Magic Damage Resistance: +25%

Armor Class: 2 (0 vs. slashing, 4 vs. crushing)

Weight: 9~

@7490 = ~When he was younger, Cernd spent a cycle of seasons meditating on his role within nature. He made no shelter, wanting to feel the land unhindered. Nature may have appreciated the intent, for she also knows that for all their dedication, at times her children can be foolish. Cernd found this cloak before the cold season set in, seemingly woven to fit him from the very undergrowth. The message was clear: He can appreciate the rain while still seeking shelter from it. Only Cernd may use this cloak.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +2
– Saving Throws: +1
– Elemental Damage Resistance: +15%
– Physical Damage Resistance: +10%
– Regeneration: +1 HP per 2 rounds

Weight: 3~

@8170 = ~Paralyzed with fear~

@50030 = ~Corthala Family Armor
This armor, long in the Corthala bloodline, protects the user against all forms of attacks. The armor has been combined with the Shadow Dragon Armor and is now even better at protecting Valygar. The armor is enchanted so that it grants a +5 bonus to Valygar's Armor Class. It also adds a bonus to resisting acid, fire, and magical damage. The armor also makes Valygar immune to charm while he wears it. Finally, the armor grants Valygar non-detection while equipped. As it is specially fitted for Valygar, only he may wear it.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Immunity to charm
– Non-Detection
– Fire Resistance: +50%
– Acid Resistance: +50%
– Magic Damage Resistance: +50%

Armor Class: 0 (-2 vs. slashing, 2 vs. crushing)

Weight: 9~

@50031 = ~Corthala Family Armor
This armor, long in the Corthala bloodline, protects the user against all forms of attacks. The armor has been combined with the Shadow Dragon Armor and is now even better at protecting Valygar. The armor is enchanted so that it grants a +5 bonus to Valygar's Armor Class. It also adds protection against Negative Energy Plane energies, Illusion and Necromancy effects, fire, and magical damage. The armor also makes Valygar immune to charm while he wears it. Finally, the armor grants Valygar non-detection while equipped. As it is specially fitted for Valygar, only he may wear it.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Immunity to charm
– Negative Plane protection
– Non-Detection
– Fire Resistance: +50%
– Magic Damage Resistance: +50%
– Saves vs. Illusion and Necromancy effects: +4

Armor Class: 0 (-2 vs. slashing, 2 vs. crushing)

Weight: 9~

@50050 = ~Improved Firecam Full-Plate Armor
This suit of armor was originally designed for Keldorn and few others may wear it. The suit was later enchanted again at <CHARNAME>'s request and it now provides Keldorn with even more protection. While equipped, the suit provides the wearer with a +2 bonus to all saving throws and grants the wearer immunity to movement-limiting effects such as Web and Grease, and fear. Despite being incredibly strong, the armor is almost weightless.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Immunity to movement-limiting effects
– Immunity to fear and panic
– Saving Throws: +2

Armor Class: -2 (-6 vs. slashing, -5 vs. piercing and missile)

Weight: 10~

@50090 = ~Keldorn distinguished himself early in his career as a paladin and received this blade as a boon from Torm. It is exceptionally accurate, but also protects him in battle with a special magical shield, and any that strike him while he wields it suffer Torm's wrath in the form of magical damage. None but Keldorn may use this sword.

With <CHARNAME>'s help and the blessing of Torm, the sword was recently re-enchanted to become even more powerful.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– 5 points of magic damage to any who damage the wielder

Combat abilities:
– Dispel Magic on each hit if a Save vs. Spell is failed
– 30% chance that the hit target is silenced for 2 rounds

THAC0: +5
Damage: 1d10+5 (slashing)
Speed Factor: 5
Proficiency Type: Two-handed Sword
Type: Two-handed

Weight: 8~

@7090 = ~This ring was given to Nalia by her father upon her ascension to adulthood. Bonded to her blood as it is, its powers may not be used by anyone else.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class and Saving Throws: +2
– Fire Resistance: +50%
– Open Locks and Find Traps: +20%
– May memorize one extra spell of each level from 1 to 5

Weight: 0~

@7222 = ~Blood Drain

In order to survive, a vampire needs sustenance. This ability will drain 1-4 points of Constitution from the target and knock them unconscious for 5 rounds. This ability may be used once per hour (5 turns).

Saving Throw: Save vs. Death~

@7223 = ~Blood Drain available for use~

@70010 = ~This is Edwin's birthright, inlaid with his family stone.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Saving Throws vs. Conjuration: +2
– Saving Throws vs. Non-Conjuration: -2
– Casting level: +1
– Extra spell slots: One extra spell slot for levels 1 and 2

Weight: 1~

@70011 = ~This is Edwin's birthright, inlaid with his family stone.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Saving Throws vs. Conjuration: +2
– Saving Throws vs. Non-Conjuration: -2
– Casting level: +2
– Extra spell slots: One extra spell slot for levels 1, 2, 3, and 4

Weight: 1~

@70020 = ~These are Eldoth's personal poisoned arrows. He learned how to use poison at a young age and can create enough venom for about 5 arrows per day. He is the only person who can safely handle these arrows.

STATISTICS:

Combat abilities:
– Hit target takes 1 point of poison damage every 2 seconds for 40 seconds (Save vs. Poison negates)

Damage: 1d6 (missile)
Launcher: Bow

Weight: 0~

@70021 = ~These are Eldoth's personal poisoned arrows. He learned how to use poison at a young age and can create enough venom for about 15 arrows per day. He is the only person who can safely handle these arrows.

STATISTICS:

Combat abilities:
– Hit target takes 1 point of poison damage every 2 seconds for 40 seconds (Save vs. Poison negates)

Damage: 1d6 (missile)
Launcher: Bow

